LEGISLATURE OF NEBRASKA
ONE HUNDRED NINTH LEGISLATURE
SECOND SESSION
LEGISLATIVE BILL 778
Introduced by Dungan, 26.
Read first time January 07, 2026
Committee: Revenue
1 A BILL FOR AN ACT relating to the Civic and Community Center Financing
2 Act; to amend section 13-2706, Revised Statutes Cumulative
3 Supplement, 2024; to change eligibility requirements and authorized
4 amounts for grants of assistance; and to repeal the original
5 section.
6 Be it enacted by the people of the State of Nebraska,
-1-

LB778 LB778
2026 2026
1 Section 1. Section 13-2706, Revised Statutes Cumulative Supplement,
2 2024, is amended to read:
3 13-2706 (1) Except as provided in subsection (2) of this section for
4 a city of the primary class, any municipality that has applied for and
5 received a grant of assistance under the Sports Arena Facility Financing
6 Assistance Act shall not receive state assistance under the Civic and
7 Community Center Financing Act for the same project for which the grant
8 was awarded under the Sports Arena Facility Financing Assistance Act.
9 (2) A city of the primary class shall not be eligible to receive a
10 grant of assistance from the Civic and Community Center Financing Act if
11 the city has applied for and received a grant of assistance under the
12 Sports Arena Facility Financing Assistance Act.
13 (3) Any city that has received funding under the Convention Center
14 Facility Financing Assistance Act shall not receive state assistance
15 under the Civic and Community Center Financing Act.
16 (4) From July 1, 2027 2023, to June 30, 2028 2024, a municipality
17 shall be eligible for a grant of assistance under the Civic and Community
18 Center Financing Act only if such municipality (a) partners with a
19 certified creative district and (b) is not prohibited from receiving a
20 grant of assistance under subsection (1), (2), or (3) of this section. In
21 awarding grants of assistance, the department shall give preference to
22 any municipality that is partnered with a certified creative district.
23 Notwithstanding the limitations on the amount of grants of assistance in
24 section 13-2705, the department may award grants of assistance to
25 qualifying municipalities in amounts set by the Nebraska Arts Council,
26 which shall not be less than one hundred thousand dollars. The department
27 shall coordinate with the Nebraska Arts Council for purposes of setting
28 such amounts. For purposes of this subsection, certified creative
29 district means a creative district certified pursuant to subdivision (5)
30 of section 82-312. After June 30, 2028 2024, this subsection no longer
31 applies.
-2-

